hc:promote-longer-arc          a fair2r:HumanContribution ;
    rdfs:label "Researcher endorsement: promote the future-research-infrastructure claim into the Conclusion's call-to-action"@en ;
    fair2r:contributedBy agent:human-author ;
    fair2r:contributionType "structural-decision" ;
    fair2r:contributionLeverage "medium" ;
    rdfs:comment "After §3.6 was added, the model offered to promote the future-research-infrastructure claim into the Conclusion so the position-paper closer carries the forward-looking argument; researcher endorsed with 'yes'. New 'The longer arc' paragraph in conclusion.tex now restates the claim with a reference back to §3.6 and the Helmholtz cross-centre graph. The position-paper closer ends on the forward-looking note before the closing aphorism."@en ;
    dcterms:created "2026-05-06"^^xsd:date ;
    prov:influenced ent:section-conclusion .

hc:research-infrastructure      a fair2r:HumanContribution ;
    rdfs:label "Researcher claims: bioinformatics precedent + future-research-infrastructure vision"@en ;
    fair2r:contributedBy agent:human-author ;
    fair2r:contributionType "content-prompt" ;
    fair2r:contributionLeverage "high" ;
    rdfs:comment "Researcher proposed two paired forward-looking claims during session: (a) 'future research success might depend a lot more on provenance models for hypothesis development, graph interconnectivity (Helmholtz graph supercharged) and clever experimental validation', and (b) 'bioinformatics was driven there earlier by the at-the-time obscene amounts of data leading to semantic tagging becoming the norm to identify genes'. Both graduated to paper text as a new subsection §3.6 of pattern.tex. The bioinformatics-precedent argument is anchored on Ashburner et al. 2000 (Gene Ontology); the Helmholtz cross-centre graph reuses curdt2025hmc. The marketing-verb 'supercharged' was rephrased to 'fully-instrumented' to fit the DLR voice."@en ;
    dcterms:created "2026-05-06"^^xsd:date ;
    prov:influenced ent:section-pattern-research-infrastructure ,
                    claim:bioinformatics-precedent ,
                    claim:future-research-infrastructure .

