    fair2r:verificationState verif:ai-confirmed .

claim:formal-methods-cousin  a fair2r:Claim ;
    rdfs:label "F(AI)^2R is structurally a cousin of model checking and theorem proving: each fair2r:Claim is a conjecture, the verification ladder is a proof-state machine, the audit pass is a proof-checker, SHACL shapes are invariants, the handback discipline is the prover/checker separation. Two useful imports we have not yet drawn on: counter-example witnesses attached to retracted claims, and lemma libraries of vetted claims that successor papers can cite by IRI without re-verifying."@en ;
    prov:wasAttributedTo agent:human-author ;
    prov:wasDerivedFrom  src:clarke2009modelchecking , src:klein2009sel4 ;
    fair2r:verificationState verif:human-confirmed ;
    dcterms:created "2026-05-07"^^xsd:date .

hc:formal-methods-relationship  a fair2r:HumanContribution ;
    rdfs:label "Researcher claim: F(AI)^2R relates to model checking / automatic theorem proving"@en ;
    fair2r:contributedBy agent:human-author ;
    fair2r:contributionType "content-prompt" ;
    fair2r:contributionLeverage "high" ;
    rdfs:comment "Researcher proposed: 'i see a relationship between the current method of the paper and model checking or automatic proofing'. Graduated to paper text as a new paragraph in §11 (Related Work) titled 'Formal methods: model checking and theorem proving.' The paragraph maps the F(AI)^2R machinery onto formal-methods vocabulary --- conjecture / proof-state / proof-checker / invariants / prover-checker separation --- and names two future-work imports the analogy suggests: counter-example witnesses on retracted claims, and lemma libraries that successor papers can cite by IRI. Hedged: 'the analogy is partial --- a manuscript is not a transition system'. Two new bib entries: clarke2009modelchecking (CACM 2009 Turing-lecture) and klein2009sel4 (SOSP 2009)."@en ;
    dcterms:created "2026-05-07"^^xsd:date ;
    prov:influenced claim:formal-methods-cousin .

hc:fix-beamer-enumitem-conflict  a fair2r:HumanContribution ;
    rdfs:label "User pasted the Beamer log; root cause = enumitem + Beamer enumerate-template conflict; fix = drop enumitem"@en ;
    fair2r:contributedBy agent:human-author ;
    fair2r:contributionType "corrective-intervention" ;
    fair2r:contributionLeverage "high" ;
    rdfs:comment "User pasted the conference-30min.log tail from the failing build-slides workflow. Root cause located: 'TeX capacity exceeded, sorry [grouping levels=255]. \\labelenumi -> { \\labelenumi }' --- a recursive macro definition triggered by loading enumitem alongside Beamer's \\setbeamertemplate{enumerate item} (in slides/style/fair2r-beamer.sty). The pitch deck compiled because it never used \\begin{enumerate}; the conference deck did. Fix: removed \\usepackage{enumitem} from slides/conference-30min.tex and stripped the [leftmargin=...,itemsep=...] options from all three \\begin{enumerate} calls. Plain Beamer enumerate is sufficient at slide scale; the visual difference is negligible. Earlier defensive commits (PR #21 fair2r-beamer.sty cleanups, TikZ removal) were unrelated to the actual bug; the TikZ figures could be restored safely now but are kept as compact-tabular for now to keep the fix minimal."@en ;
    dcterms:created "2026-05-07"^^xsd:date ;
    prov:influenced ent:slidedeck-conference .

hc:reconcile-illustrate-scrutinize  a fair2r:HumanContribution ;
    rdfs:label "Researcher request: continue with open tasks; reconcile provenance; generate illustration where positive and scrutinize"@en ;
    fair2r:contributedBy agent:human-author ;
    fair2r:contributionType "rule-shape" ;
    fair2r:contributionLeverage "medium" ;
    rdfs:comment "Three things in one PR: (1) provenance reconciliation: paper/sections/discussion.tex and paper/sections/acknowledgements.tex deleted (they were marked superseded after the position-paper reframe and unreferenced); the act:rev-reconcile-and-illustrate activity records a prov:Invalidation of ent:section-discussion. (2) New illustration: paper/figures/eight-practices.tex, a 4x2 grid of the eight practices colour-coded by the failure-mode family each addresses (evidence-trail / drift-prevention / artefact-discipline / legal-institutional). Loaded from sections/eight-practices.tex. (3) Scrutiny: scanned all section files for voice issues. The Author's Note's direct address is preserved as a documented genre exception (claim:authors-note-voice-exception); agents/scientific-writer.md updated to make the carve-out explicit. self-reference.tex's closing aphorism reworded once to remove a second 'you'."@en ;
    dcterms:created "2026-05-07"^^xsd:date ;
    prov:influenced ent:figure-eight-practices ,
                    claim:authors-note-voice-exception ,
                    ent:prompt-scientific-writer .

hc:journal-decline           a fair2r:HumanContribution ;
    rdfs:label "Researcher claim: traditional publishing under stress; journal-as-distribution may be in decline; new forms of scientific communication"@en ;
    fair2r:contributedBy agent:human-author ;
    fair2r:contributionType "content-prompt" ;
    fair2r:contributionLeverage "high" ;
    rdfs:comment "Researcher proposed during session: 'traditional publishing under Stress due many slop papers, original concept of journals as distribution (even Internet supported) might be in decline. new forms of scientific communication'. Graduated to paper text as a new third paragraph in §1 of intro.tex titled 'The journal as distribution channel may be in decline.' The paragraph is hedged: 'we do not claim the journal is dead' but 'the assumption that the journal is the unproblematic default ... can no longer be taken for granted'. Three new bib entries (eisen2018preprints, tennant2016open, conroy2023sleuths), all lit-retrieved, identifier-verified to the extent possible without full-text reading. New claim:journal-as-distribution-in-decline at human-confirmed."@en ;
    dcterms:created "2026-05-07"^^xsd:date ;
    prov:influenced claim:journal-as-distribution-in-decline .

hc:reconcile-default-branch-and-pages-source  a fair2r:HumanContribution ;
    rdfs:label "Reconcile: main is the default branch; Pages source = GitHub Actions"@en ;
    fair2r:contributedBy agent:human-author ;
    fair2r:contributionType "rule-shape" ;
    fair2r:contributionLeverage "high" ;
    rdfs:comment "User performed two repo-settings changes: (a) switched the default branch to main; (b) set Pages source to GitHub Actions. Repository docs reconciled: CLAUDE.md branch-policy paragraph rewritten (main is default; development on feature branches off main; PRs target main; direct pushes to main require explicit instruction); CLAUDE.md gains a 'Pages source' subsection naming pages.yml as the canonical deploy mechanism. agents/orchestrator.md refusal-conditions updated. doc/methodology.md gains a 'Branch and deployment policy' subsection. pages.yml itself does not change; its configure-pages + upload-pages-artefact + deploy-pages chain is the canonical pattern for 'Source = GitHub Actions'."@en ;
    dcterms:created "2026-05-07"^^xsd:date ;
    prov:influenced ent:workflow-pages .

hc:fix-beamer-conference-build-attempt-2  a fair2r:HumanContribution ;
    rdfs:label "Second attempt at fixing the conference-deck Beamer compile: log-dump-on-failure + replace inline TikZ"@en ;
    fair2r:contributedBy agent:human-author ;
    fair2r:contributionType "corrective-intervention" ;
    fair2r:contributionLeverage "medium" ;
    rdfs:comment "Attempt 1 (PR #21 first commit) failed CI as well. Two changes: (1) build-slides.yml now runs latex-action with continue_on_error=true and adds an `if: failure()` step that tails the .log file into the workflow output; the next failure will show actual LaTeX error lines without auth. (2) The two inline TikZ figures in conference-30min.tex (ten-stage pipeline, verification ladder) are replaced with simpler tabular and framed-text layouts; TikZ is the most likely culprit and removing it restores a compilable deck while we wait for the log to confirm. Pitch deck unchanged."@en ;
    dcterms:created "2026-05-07"^^xsd:date ;
    prov:influenced ent:workflow-build-slides ,
                    ent:slidedeck-conference .

hc:pages-staleness-fix       a fair2r:HumanContribution ;
    rdfs:label "Researcher report: the deployed Pages site does not seem up to date"@en ;
    fair2r:contributedBy agent:human-author ;
    fair2r:contributionType "corrective-intervention" ;
    fair2r:contributionLeverage "low" ;
    rdfs:comment "Researcher reported the Pages site appears stale after PR #19. Sandbox cannot fetch the live URL to confirm. Three defensive fixes: (1) scripts/build_provenance_site.py now writes _site/.nojekyll so GitHub Pages does not run Jekyll on the artefact (Jekyll can misbehave on the static/ tree); (2) the page template's hero section gains a visible build-tag printing the cache-bust hash, so the researcher can confirm at a glance which bundle their browser is rendering; (3) touching scripts/build_provenance_site.py and site/static/style.css matches pages.yml's path filter, so the merge triggers a fresh pages.yml run and forces the CDN cache (max-age=600) to refresh."@en ;
    dcterms:created "2026-05-06"^^xsd:date ;
    prov:influenced ent:script-build-provenance-site .

hc:beamer-only-slides        a fair2r:HumanContribution ;
    rdfs:label "Researcher decision: only ship Beamer (drop Marp); equivalent Beamer is OK as well"@en ;
    fair2r:contributedBy agent:human-author ;
    fair2r:contributionType "structural-decision" ;
    fair2r:contributionLeverage "high" ;
    rdfs:comment "After the Marp asset-inlining fix landed (PR #18), the researcher decided 'only ship beamer'. Beamer reuses the existing LaTeX toolchain (xu-cheng/latex-action), the DLR colours from paper/style/fair2r.sty, and the same TikZ idiom as the paper figures; no Chromium / Node / Marp / theme-inlining preprocessor. New slides/style/fair2r-beamer.sty is the slide companion to paper/style/fair2r.sty (mid-grey frame titles, DLR-Blue accent rule, hairline rules, the \\sectiondivider helper). Both decks rewritten in Beamer; slides/Makefile and the build-slides workflow now use latexmk + xu-cheng/latex-action mirroring paper/Makefile and build-paper.yml. README and site/index.md updated to point at the Beamer PDFs only (no PPTX); CLAUDE.md and doc/methodology.md primary-artefact list updated to .tex sources; agents/presentation.md rewritten as Beamer-only with explicit refusal to reintroduce a Marp / HTML / PPTX path."@en ;
    dcterms:created "2026-05-06"^^xsd:date ;
    prov:influenced ent:slide-style ,
                    ent:slidedeck-pitch ,
                    ent:slidedeck-conference ,
                    ent:workflow-build-slides .

