# Human-authored prompt for the repair pass + AI mirror

hc:prov-curator-repair-pass-2026-05-07  a fair2r:HumanContribution ;
    rdfs:label "Researcher prompt: run provenance-curator repair pass with per-defect reasons + WIP topology-page transparency"@en ;
    fair2r:contributedBy agent:human-author ;
    fair2r:contributionType "rule-shape" ;
    fair2r:contributionLeverage "high" ;
    rdfs:comment "User dispatched the provenance-curator subagent to repair the 8 fair2r:Claim entities surfaced by the topology page's Worked verification example as missing prov:wasGeneratedBy. The prompt added two binding shapes beyond the repair itself: (a) capture, per defect, a one-sentence reason as an rdfs:comment on a new repair activity, so the cooperative process can learn from the pattern --- 'we can learn for our collaborative process'; (b) make the topology page an honest two-state walkthrough (WIP disclaimer + BEFORE table preserved + AFTER table added + 'Why those edges were missing' subsection + forward-looking next-likely-defect line), not a sanitised after-image. Schema growth made explicit: fair2r:repairs added as an owl:ObjectProperty (domain prov:Activity, range fair2r:Claim) per the curator agent rule that schema growth must be explicit. Output also appends the cooperative-process observation to doc/user-observations-log.md (hypothesis stage; suggests a 'no claim without a parent activity' refusal rule for agents/provenance-curator.md)."@en ;
    dcterms:created "2026-05-07"^^xsd:date ;
    prov:influenced act:provenance-verification-pass ,
                    act:repair-claim-domain-ontologies-extension ,
                    act:repair-claim-reproducibility-baseline-poor ,
                    act:repair-claim-reviewer-side-ai-policies ,
                    act:repair-claim-bioinformatics-precedent ,
                    act:repair-claim-journal-as-distribution-in-decline ,
                    act:repair-claim-authors-note-voice-exception ,
                    act:repair-claim-formal-methods-cousin ,
                    act:repair-claim-contribution-tracking-rule .

ai:prov-curator-repair-pass-2026-05-07  a fair2r:AIContribution ;
    rdfs:label "Provenance-curator subagent: 8 missing prov:wasGeneratedBy edges repaired in the open, with per-defect reasons captured"@en ;
    fair2r:contributedBy agent:provenance-curator ;
    fair2r:contributionType "rule-shape" ;
    fair2r:contributionLeverage "high" ;
    rdfs:comment "Provenance-curator subagent ran the SPARQL conformance query against the live graph, classified each of the 8 defective claims by reason (5 had no parent activity in the landing commit; 3 had a parent activity but the symmetric edge on the claim was dropped at curator time), minted 5 synthetic act:meta-cooperation-<date>-<slug> activities for the parentless claims, attached the existing act:rev-* activity for the other 3, and recorded a per-claim repair activity carrying fair2r:repairs and a one-sentence rdfs:comment. Topology page rewritten as an honest two-state walkthrough. Cooperative-process observation appended to doc/user-observations-log.md as 'Why audited defects are pedagogical, not embarrassing' (hypothesis stage). Schema growth: fair2r:repairs added explicitly. rdflib re-parse: 1736 -> 1906 triples (+170), clean. Post-repair conformance query: 0 rows."@en ;
    dcterms:created "2026-05-07"^^xsd:date ;
    prov:influenced act:provenance-verification-pass ,
                    act:repair-claim-domain-ontologies-extension ,
                    act:repair-claim-reproducibility-baseline-poor ,
                    act:repair-claim-reviewer-side-ai-policies ,
                    act:repair-claim-bioinformatics-precedent ,
                    act:repair-claim-journal-as-distribution-in-decline ,
                    act:repair-claim-authors-note-voice-exception ,
