    rdfs:comment "Researcher proposed a bridging-responsibility claim during the iterative session: senior researchers who lived through pre-LLM scholarship are positioned (analogously to Xennials, who lived through pre-internet daily life) to articulate the disciplines and constraints a tooling-native cohort cannot reconstruct unaided. Activity minted at claim-add time so the claim is born with a generating parent rather than retroactively repaired."@en .

claim:senior-researcher-bridge  a fair2r:Claim ;
    rdfs:label "Senior researchers --- analogous to the Xennial bridge generation --- carry a responsibility to articulate, in machine-readable form, the previously-unthinkable-to-question scholarly disciplines so they survive translation into a tooling-native research culture; F(AI)^2R is one such articulation."@en ;
    prov:wasGeneratedBy act:meta-cooperation-2026-05-07-senior-researcher-bridge ;
