hc:senior-researcher-bridge-claim  a fair2r:HumanContribution ;
    rdfs:label "Researcher claim: senior researchers have a Xennial-like bridging responsibility to articulate previously unthinkable disciplines"@en ;
    fair2r:contributedBy agent:human-author ;
    fair2r:contributionType "content-prompt" ;
    fair2r:contributionLeverage "high" ;
    rdfs:comment "Researcher proposed: 'we as senior researchers who know the way how things were done and why they were done that have a responsibility to help build bridges to the unthinkable of the past (a similar situation as xennials)'. Graduated to paper text as a new paragraph in the Conclusion titled 'The bridge to what is now unthinkable.', positioned between 'The longer arc.' and the closing emphasis line. The paragraph names the Xennial generational analogue (born late enough to remember pre-internet working life, early enough to have spent professional life inside it), maps it onto senior researchers who span pre-LLM and LLM-era scholarship, and frames F(AI)^2R as one articulation of disciplines that a tooling-native cohort cannot reconstruct unaided. One new bib entry: shafer2014xennials (lit-retrieved). The claim is born with a parent activity (act:meta-cooperation-2026-05-07-senior-researcher-bridge) per the no-parentless-claim rule from the 2026-05-07 curator pass."@en ;
    dcterms:created "2026-05-07"^^xsd:date ;
    prov:influenced claim:senior-researcher-bridge .

